title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: Clayton
description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Return
description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

title: The Kiss
description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

title: The Game
description: The Wattersons embark on their first family game of Dodge or Dare, but soon find out why Gumball and Darwin abandoned the monster they created.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: Sarah
description: Darwin asks Sarah for a photo to put on the cover of the school yearbook. But when Sarah tries to help, things get a little sticky. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Teachers
description: When Darwin asks his friends which teacher deserves to be on the yearbook cover, they struggle to find a single worthy candidate! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Alan
description: Darwin wants to put Alan on the cover of the school yearbook - but Alan's apparent modesty gets in the way. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Plan
description: The Watterson kids come up with a fool-proof plan to save their mom, but is it Gumball-proof?

title: Banana Joe
description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Pineapple
description: Gumball briefly loses his puppet mouth to an enthusiastic Pineapple.

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: The Check
description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais are delighted when Grandpa Louie gives them a check for $5000. They immediately start fantasizing over what to spend it on. But when Mom and Dad say they're going to spend the money on paying bills instead, it's a race to the bank to see who can cash the check first.

title: The Sidekick
description: During a quest to retrieve a loaned video game, Darwin begins to suspect that he is trapped playing second fiddle to Gumball.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: The Advice
description: Mr. Small feels that he hasn't inspired the children of Elmore Junior High, so Gumball and Darwin try to lift his spirits.

title: The Remote
description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

title: The Ghost
description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

title: The Promise
description: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

title: Waiting for Gumball: Infinite Loop
description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Clean
description: Grady is determined to tidy up the house and persuades Howdy and Frank to help. While cleaning Frank unexpectedly discovers the love of his life under a bin bag.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Cool to Be Felt
description: Gumball and Darwin realize they are puppets and it's seriously cool.

title: The Quest
description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais rescue her doll from Tina Rex.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Bored
description: Frank is bored and pesters the others to entertain him for the afternoon.

title: Carrie
description: Darwin sets out to find a photo of Carrie for the cover of the school yearbook - but they end up reminiscing about all their past spooky shenanigans. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Helmet
description: Gumball's magic tinfoil helmet threatens to tear the Watterson family apart!

title: The Apprentice
description: Gumball decides that the best way to prove to Mr. Fitzgerald that he's good enough for Penny is to become his apprentice for the day. The problem is Mr. Fitzgerald has an important interview and Gumball's enthusiastic attempts to help him might actually do more harm than good, both to Mr. Fitzgerald's business and to Gumball's future with Penny.

title: The Comic
description: Gumball is the star of his own comic, but struggles to match up to his heroic alter-ego.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Gnomes
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that anything they imagine will become real in Puppet World, but all they can think of are Garden Gnomes.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.

title: The Refund
description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.
